SET r.original_relation = 'authored', r.t_obs = [1766102400.0], r.atomic_facts = ['[References] Acemoglu, D., and P. Restrepo. 2020. \'Robots and Jobs: Evidence From US Labor Markets.\' Journal of Political Economy 128, no. 6: 2188-2244. https:// doi. org/ 10. 1086/ 705716. Acemoglu, D., and P. Restrepo. 2021. \'Demographics and Automation.\' Review of Economic Studies 89, no. 1: 1-44. https:// doi. org/ 10. 1093/ restud/ rdab031. Agrawal, A., U. Mukherjee, and S. Muthulingam. 2020. \'Does Organizational Forgetting Affect Quality Knowledge Gained Through Spillover?-Evidence From the Automotive Industry.\' Production and Operations Management 29, no. 4: 907-934. https:// doi. org/ 10. 1111/ poms. 13137 . Ahmadi, T., A. F. Hesaraki, and J. P. M. Morsch. 2025. \'Exploring IT- Driven Supply Chain Capabilities and Resilience: The Roles of Supply Chain Risk Management and Complexity.\' Supply Chain Management- An International Journal 30, no. 1: 50-66. https:// doi. org/ 10. 1108/ scm- 11- 2023- 0561. Alikhani, R., A. Ranjbar, A. Jamali, S. A. Torabi, and C. W. Zobel. 2023. \'Towards Increasing Synergistic Effects of Resilience Strategies in Supply Chain Network Design.\' Omega 116: 102819. https:// doi. org/ 10. 1016/j. omega. 2022. 102819. Antonioli, D., A. Marzucchi, F. Rentocchini, and S. Vannuccini. 2024. \'Robot Adoption and Product Innovation.\' Research Policy 53, no. 6: 105002. https:// doi. org/ 10. 1016/j. respol. 2024. 105002. Armstrong, B., and J. Shah. 2023. \'A Smarter Strategy for Using Robots Automation Should Focus More on Flexibilliv Than on Productivity.\' Harvard Business Review 101, no. 3-4: 35-42. Baldwin, R., and J. Lopez- Gonzalez. 2015. \'Supply- Chain Trade: A Portrait of Global Patterns and Several Testable Hypotheses.\' World Economy 38, no. 11: 1682-1721. https:// doi. org/ 10. 1111/ twec. 12189 . Bartik, T. J. 1991. Who Benefits From State and Local Economic Development Policies? W.E. Upjohn Institute. http:// www. jstor. org/ stable/ j. ctvh4 zh1q. Benhabib, J., J. Perla, and C. Tonetti. 2021. \'Reconciling Models of Diffusion and Innovation: A Theory of the Productivity Distribution and Technology Frontier.\' Econometrica 89, no. 5: 2261-2301. https:// doi. org/ 10. 3982/ ECTA1 5020. Bianchi, N., and M. Giorcelli. 2022. \'The Dynamics and Spillovers of Management Interventions: Evidence From the Training Within Industry Program.\' Journal of Political Economy 130, no. 6: 1630-1675. https:// doi. org/ 10. 1086/ 719277. Birkel, H., and J. M. Müller. 2025. \'Resilient by Nature or Technology? How Industry 4.0 Enhances Supply Chain Resilience Until 2035.\' Supply Chain Management: An International Journal 30: 304-322. https:// doi. org/ 10. 1108/ SCM- 07- 2023- 0340. Blaettchen, P., A. P. Calmon, and G. Hall. 2025. \'Traceability Technology Adoption in Supply Chain Networks.\' Management Science 71, no. 1: 83-102. https:// doi. org/ 10. 1287/ mnsc. 2022. 01759 . Bodrožić, Z., and S. Adler. 2022. \'Alternative Futures for the Digital Transformation: A Macro- Level Schumpeterian Perspective.\' Organization Science 33, no. 1: 105-125. https:// doi. org/ 10. 1287/ orsc. 2021. 1558. Brau, R., J. Aloysius, and E. Siemsen. 2023. \'Demand Planning for the Digital Supply Chain: How to Integrate Human Judgment and Predictive Analytics.\' Journal of Operations Management 69, no. 6: 965-982. https:// doi. org/ 10. 1002/ joom. 1257. Cao, Q., E. Gedajlovic, and H. Zhang. 2009. \'Unpacking Organizational Ambidexterity: Dimensions, Contingencies, and Synergistic Effects.\' Organization Science 20, no. 4: 781-796. https:// doi. org/ 10. 1287/ orsc. 1090. 0426. Cao, Q., X. Geng, and J. Zhang. 2022. \'Impact of Channel Structure on a Manufacturer\'s Bundling Decision With an Application to Digital Goods.\' Production and Operations Management 31, no. 4: 1679-1697. https:// doi. org/ 10. 1111/ poms. 13638 . Caselli, M., A. Fracasso, S. Scicchitano, S. Traverso, and E. Tundis. 2025. \'What Workers and Robots Do: An Activity- Based Analysis of the Impact of Robotization on Changes in Local Employment.\' Research Policy 54, no. 1: 105135. https:// doi. org/ 10. 1016/j. respol. 2024. 105135. Chen, L., T. Li, F. Jia, and T. Schoenherr. 2023. \'The Impact of Governmental COVID- 19 Measures on Manufacturers\' Stock Market Valuations: The Role of Labor Intensity and Operational Slack.\' Journal of Operations Management 69, no. 3: 404-425. https:// doi. org/ 10. 1002/ joom. 1207. Chen, Y., B. Li, and B. Huo. 2025. \'Building Operational Resilience Through Digitalization: The Roles of Supply Chain Network Position.\' Technological Forecasting and Social Change 211: 123918. https:// doi. org/ 10. 1016/j. techf ore. 2024. 123918. Chu, Y., X. Tian, and W. Wang. 2019. \'Corporate Innovation Along the Supply Chain.\' Management Science 65, no. 6: 2445-2466. https:// doi. org/ 10. 1287/ mnsc. 2017. 2924. Cilekoglu, A. A., R. Moreno, and R. Ramos. 2024. \'The Impact of Robot Adoption on Global Sourcing.\' Research Policy 53, no. 3: 104953. https:// doi. org/ 10. 1016/j. respol. 2024. 104953. Ciulli, F., A. Kolk, and S. Boe- Lillegraven. 2020. \'Circularity Brokers: Digital Platform Organizations and Waste Recovery in Food Supply Chains.\' Journal of Business Ethics 167, no. 2: 299-331. https:// doi. org/ 10. 1007/ s1055 1- 019- 04160 - 5. Cohen, M., S. Cui, S. Doetsch, et al. 2022. \'Bespoke Supply- Chain Resilience: The Gap Between Theory and Practice.\' Journal of Operations Management 68, no. 5: 515-531. https:// doi. org/ 10. 1002/ joom. 1184. Costello, A. M. 2020. \'Credit Market Disruptions and Liquidity Spillover Effects in the Supply Chain.\' Journal of Political Economy 128, no. 9: 3434-3468. https:// doi. org/ 10. 1086/ 708736. De Vito, A., M. Jacob, D. Schindler, and G. Xu. 2025. \'How Do Corporate Tax Hikes Affect Investment Allocation Within Multinationals?\' Review of Finance 29, no. 2: 531-565. https:// doi. org/ 10. 1093/ rof/ rfaf006. Dixit, A., and J. E. Stiglitz. 1977. \'Monopolistic Competition and Optimum Product Diversity.\' American Economic Review 67: 297-308. Dixon, J., B. Hong, and L. Wu. 2021. \'The Robot Revolution: Managerial and Employment Consequences for Firms.\' Management Science 67, no. 9: 5586-5605. https:// doi. org/ 10. 1287/ mnsc. 2020. 3812. Feigenbaum, J., and D. P. Gross. 2024. \'Answering the Call of Automation: How the Labor Market Adjusted to Mechanizing Telephone Operation.\' Quarterly Journal of Economics 139, no. 3: 18791939. https:// doi. org/ 10. 1093/ qje/ qjae005. Femano, A. L., and T. Breitbach. 2025. \'Measuring Supply Chain Resilience for Informed Resilience Strategy Investment.\' Transportation Journal 64, no. 1: e12037. https:// doi. org/ 10. 1002/ tjo3. 12037'], r.t_start = [1608336000.0], r.edge_row = 193;
